## Authentication

### Two-Legged OAuth (Client Credentials)

For server-to-server integrations using client credentials:

```python
from blackboard_lms import Client

client = Client(
    domain="your-institution.blackboard.com",
    client_id="your-client-id",
    client_secret="your-client-secret",
)
```

### Three-Legged OAuth (Authorization Code + PKCE)

For user-delegated access (e.g., acting on behalf of a student or instructor):

```python
from blackboard_lms import OAuth2Client, AuthConfig, Client

auth = OAuth2Client(AuthConfig(
    base_url="https://your-institution.blackboard.com",
    client_id="your-client-id",
    client_secret="your-client-secret",
))

# Step 1: Generate the authorization URL with PKCE
result = auth.get_authorization_url(
    redirect_uri="https://your-app.com/callback",
    scope="read",
    state="random-csrf-token",
)
# Redirect the user to result.url, store result.code_verifier

# Step 2: After the user authorizes, exchange the code
auth.exchange_code(
    code=code_from_callback,
    redirect_uri="https://your-app.com/callback",
    code_verifier=result.code_verifier,
)

# Step 3: Use the authenticated client
client = Client(
    domain="your-institution.blackboard.com",
    client_id="your-client-id",
    client_secret="your-client-secret",
)
client.set_access_token(auth.get_token())
```

## Quick Start

```python
# List courses
courses = client.courses.list()
print(courses)

# Get a single course
course = client.courses.get("externalId:INTRO-101")
print(course.name)
```

## Error Handling

```python
from blackboard_lms import NotFoundError, RateLimitError, APIError

try:
    course = client.courses.get("_invalid_id_")
except NotFoundError:
    print("Course not found")
except RateLimitError as e:
    print(f"Rate limited — retry after {e.retry_after}s")
except APIError as e:
    print(f"API error {e.status_code}: {e.message}")
```

## Pagination

Paginated methods return iterators:

```python
for course in client.courses.list():
    print(course.name)
```

